main event: A UFO was observed on 22nd July 1953 at 1010 South Rd., G.I.L.W., Calif. It was described as a Venuslike object moving erratically with flashing lights, likely a conventional aircraft or fireball.
interesting points: The object was observed for 1 1/2 minutes and was seen to move from horizon to horizon in that time
The UFO was described as giving off bright light and moving in an erratic manner
The source of the report is listed as Long Beach Control Tower and a ground visual from an aircraft service mechanic
No physical evidence or photographs were provided as proof of the sighting
The conclusion in the report suggested that the object could have been a conventional aircraft or a fireball
witnesses: Long Beach Control Tower, aircraft service mechanic, and weather observer
